<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section class="section relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-20"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-12 animate-on-scroll">
            <span class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</span>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-display font-bold text-white">Common Questions</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6 stagger-children">
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">How long does it take to build webhooks from scratch?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">Plan for 3+ engineering sprints minimum. Retry logic, dead letter queues, HMAC signatures, delivery monitoring, subscriber management, endpoint health checking. And that is before your first customer finds a bug.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What is the hidden cost of building your own?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">Retry queue maintenance, edge case handling (timeouts, redirects, certificate errors), monitoring dashboards, rate limiting, log storage, subscriber onboarding. None of this stops after v1 ships. It compounds.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">How quickly can I integrate Hook0?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">Under 30 minutes. One API call to trigger an event. SDKs for Python, Node.js, and others if you prefer.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Can I migrate from a homegrown system?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">Yes. REST API and SDKs, so you can run both systems in parallel during migration. No big bang cutover required.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

